<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-03T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-03T16:00:00-05:00" n="730" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d730">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/10352a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BRC1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-03T17:00:00-04:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">June 3, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s May 31, 3 p.m. Department is advised by French Embassy here
                            that French wireless station in Liberia cannot be put in condition for
                            service for some time and that meanwhile it is necessary to utilize the
                            German wireless station. Cable if Liberian Government is offering
                            objection to use of German station.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>